Description: Small scripts to use with BunsenLabs.
 A collection of small scripts to provide various functions
 which might be useful to BunsenLinux users and system administrators.
 .
  - beepmein: Alarm clock script based on 'at'.
  - bl-conky-edit: Script to find and edit conky config files.
  - bl-conky-manager: Yad-based conky manager.
  - bl-conkymove: Script to assist the relocation of conky windows.
  - bl-conky-session: Script to handle multiple conky sessions.
  - bl-image-upload: Generic image upload utility.
  - bl-imgbb-upload: Screenshot and image upload utility for imgbb.
  - bl-imgur-upload: Screenshot and image upload utility for imgur.
  - bl-kb: Script to manage openbox keyboard shortcuts.
  - bl-lock: Script to lock the display.
  - bl-notify-broadcast: Script to send user notifications from root processes.
  - bl-obthemes: Script to save or restore desktop gui theme configurations.
  - bl-pkg-versions: Utility to display the versions of BunsenLabs packages.
  - bl-reload-gtk23: Script to notify clients of GTK2/3 configuration changes.
  - bl-restart: Script to restart all instances of a process name.
  - bl-setlocale: Yad-based script to set user's locale.
  - bl-tint2-edit: Script to find and edit tint2 config files.
  - bl-tint2-manager: Yad-based tint2 manager.
  - bl-tint2-session: Script to handle multiple tint2 sessions.
  - bl-urxlx: Script to convert Xresources colours to rgb for lxterminal.
  - bl-xbk: Script to manage xbindkeys keyboard shortcuts.
  - bl-xinerama-prop: Script to get xinerama properties in a shell script.

